We can use the information given in the box to convert decagrams to grams and grams to milligrams. 

Since 1 decagram is equal to 10 grams, we know that a 2-decagram container is equal to 20 grams. 

Since 1,000 milligrams is equal to 1 gram, we can convert 20 grams to milligrams by multiplying by 1,000: 

\begin{align*}
20\text{ grams}\cdot 1000 \frac{\text{milligrams}}{\text{gram}} &= 20,000 \text{ milligrams}
\end{align*}

So there are 20,000 milligrams in one 2-decagram container. 

To find the number of 1-milligram doses, we divide the total number of milligrams by 1 milligram per dose: 

\begin{align*}
\frac{20,000\text{ milligrams}}{1\text{ milligram per dose}} &= 20,000 \text{ doses}
\end{align*}

Therefore, the answer is $\boxed{\textbf{(D) } 20,000}$.
